Judgment of eviction granted. Defendant(s) to vacate the premises located at 807 East Timber Drive #8, Rhinelander, County of Oneida, State of Wisconsin.

column1: IT IS HEREBY ORDERED:

1. Plaintiffs motion to lift the stay on the eviction granted November 2, 2020 is GRANTED upon a finding that the defendant has failed to comply with requirements for protection under the COVID-19 eviction moratorium imposed by the Center For Disease Control.
2. Defendant shall vacate the rental premises located at 807 East Timber Drive Apt. # 8, Rhinelander, WI 54501, together with all her personal belongings, on or before March 19, 2021.

3. After March 19, 2021, plaintiff has leave to obtain a Writ of Restitution (Eviction) directing the Sheriff to promptly remove the defendant and all personal property that is not property of the plaintiff from the rental premises.
4. The defendant shall provide to plaintiffs counsel a true and correct copy of her state and federal income tax returns for the year 2020.
5. The defendant shall safeguard and shall not spend any portion of her anticipated state and/or federal income tax refunds until further order of the court.

6. The defendant shall safeguard and shall not spend any portion of any stimulus payment she receives that arises from state and/or federal money distributions to the public as a result of the COVID-19 pandemic until further order of the court.

7. The defendant shall promptly notify counsel for plaintiff and the court in writing upon the defendant receiving any state and/or federal income tax refund or stimulus payment, together with detail including the amount(s) received.
